article.headline: Rhode Island 60, Kent State 49
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Dustin Hellenga scored 15 points and Brian Woodward added 12 to lift Rhode Island to a 60-49 victory over Kent State on Sunday. The Rams (6-2) never trailed and responded each time the Golden Flashes (4-1) got close in the second half. Dawan Robinson made a 3-pointer and Jamal Wise hit two free throws to give the Rams a 45-38 lead after an 8-2 run pulled the Golden Flashes to 40-38 with 8:27 remaining. After John Edwards' jumper brought Kent State to 47-44 with 2:51 left, Hellenga and Woodward each made two free throws to push Rhode Island's lead to 51-44. The Rams hit 11-of-12 free throws in the final 2:23. Edwards led the Golden Flashes with 18 points. Robinson had 10 points for the Rams. Wise added eight points and eight rebounds.
